{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This group represents a maltodextrin glucosidase (MalZ). MalZ has been identified as an enzyme hydrolyzing maltotriose and longer maltodextrins to glucose and maltose [[cite:PUB00060949], [cite:PUB00060959]]. It is controlled by MatT, the transcriptional activator of the maltose system. It cleaves glucose from the reducing end of maltotriose and longer maltodextrins with a chain length of up to 7 glucose units [[cite:PUB00060949]]. Interestingly, in E. coli,  a Trp to Cys exchange at position 292 gains MalZ the ability to transfer dextrinyl moieties to glucose, maltose, and other maltodextrins [[cite:PUB00060948]]. When incubated with 5% maltotriose (G3), MalZ obtains the transglycosylation ability and helps to produce a nigerose-containing oligosaccharide in vitro [[cite:PUB00060958]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR017853", "name" "Glycoside hydrolase superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF036918" "Maltodextrin glucosidase"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Maltodextrin glucosidase", "short" "MalZ"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 125, "taxa" 1175, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1713, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1713, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1307}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommendations of the Nomenclature Committee of the International Union of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (IUBMB) and it describes each type of characterized enzyme for which an EC (Enzyme Commission) number has been provided.", "rank" 19, "accessions" [{"accession" "3.2.1.20", "url" "https://enzyme.expasy.or